templates/heat-uwsgi.ini.j2.message:
This can be generated using config_template, so I am not sure we really need a new variable.

If we want to have the convenience of defining one var for everything, can't we just have:

{% if openstack_service_timeout is defined %}
socket-timeout = {{ openstack_service_timeout }}
http-timeout = {{ openstack_service_timeout }}
{% endif %}

At the end it produces the same result, and it is very clean in terms of amount of variables.

